venue.name: U Top House of Chicken Rice

tips.text: Everything is good here ! Please come try !!

formattedAddress: Blk 1 #01-18 Tanjong Pagar Plaza (opp Amara Hotel)

tips.text: This is not an underwear shop
Just tried the crème caramel maison and the dame blanche, it was yummy ! (Tested and approved by a genuine French girl !)
Really nice drinks. Try the kingfish sashimi and the fantastic bahru boot leg. Sit at the bar because the staff is really nice!
Spicy ramen at only $5.50. Add an egg for only $0.50! DanielFoodDiary.com
Generous portions for 1 person mixed platter. Everything on the plate is very good! Must try !
Muay Thai Food is fantastic. Beware the really spicy mango salad.
Good Indian food. They have dum biriyani as well.

formattedAddress: 32 New Market St (Eu Tong Sen St)

tips.text: Yong tau foo: Lots of stalls here. 1 of them, Poy Kee Yong Tau Foo #01-1066, sees daily loyals. Fishball salty but everything else is yummy. Noodles q, chilli sauce kicking!
Bak Kwa! Minced Pork & Sliced Pork are delicious!
Only come after 1130am if you're hoping to buy the ondeh ondeh. Parking is challenging here on the weekends.
Wagyu beef and set meals! Sashimis are so fresh! Authentic Japanese! very friendly staff too! This is now officially one of my fave in Tras area.

venue.name: Shun Ka Shuu Tou (春夏秋冬)

tips.text: Unfortunately this time the lunch was rather disappointing 😩 sushi n sashimi wasn't that super fresh 😁 overall the service was good 😊

venue.name: Imperial Treasure Noodle & Congee House 御宝粥面专家

tips.text: Nice char siew e-fu noodle
The Sanji Ramen is surprisingly good, especially the roasted pork shoulder. Its soup base is superb as well.

formattedAddress: Stall 45, Maxwell Food Centre (1 Kadayanallur St.)

tips.text: Basically everything here is good. Must try their homemade tofu and porridge. Claypot frog leg is also recommended! 😍 love this place
Dumplings and gyoza. Fried spicy chicken
New Location! 33 Ereskine st. One of best restaurants in Singapore, love the truffle buratta cheese.
Real pieces of pumpkin in their pumpkin soup. Nice! #thomtotieats
Friendly & excellent service, especially for young kids. Food is ok although dessert choices not inspiring. Coffee's not bad.
Assam fish, pork rib, lady finger. Durian chendol with coconut ice cream is nice as well. The place is petit but full of peranakan flavors.
The dinosaur bone is crazy epic.
muz try their bi-bim-bab!
Tom yam pasta and chicken chop is yummy. Coffee is bad but tea is value for money.
This is the best Thai Restaurant in Singapore :)
you've gotta order the beef for the steamboat!
The raisins bread will change how you talk about bread forever
Good food good price

venue.name: Chiew Kee Chicken Noodle House 钊记油鸡面家

tips.text: Best soy sauce chicken in SG! quick service too even during peak hours as long as u dun order Noodles :p

venue.name: The Disgruntled Brasserie At The Club Hotel

tips.text: Good looking and tasty 2/3 courses set lunches available @ $28/$32++. Decent portions too.
